gomodel:SYNGO_623  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The supplemental table S1 contains proteins identified in the PSD preparation (Synaptic junctional protein preparation).\nFor proteins coming from datasets derived from PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctions) preparations without defined selection / enrichment of the pre- or postsynaptic compartment we cannot assign these proteins to excitatory and/or inhibitory nor to the presynapse or / and postsynapse without further information.. Experimental description: Briefly adult mouse brains (2-16 months, 20 animals, 10 g wet weight) were homogenized ... p. 915" ;
